docs.abstract: Examination by The New York Times of activities of WikiLeaks during founder Julian Assange's years in exile reveals organization's document releases have often benefited Russia; American officials believe that there are no direct ties between Russia and organization, which has been of concern due to possibility Russia is trying to influence presidential election with leaks related to hacking of Democratic National Committee emails; Assange says link to Russia is being advanced by Hillary Clinton and Democrats.
